@Laura

When my brother-in-law came home from Viet Nam, I came home from high school, and he and I were the only ones in the house. He said, "Let's go shopping. I need underwear." We had a fun time at the mall. Only when my sister, his wife, came home from work, did I find out he had plenty of underwear; he just didn't want to do the laundry!

Fast forward 55+ years (not bothering to count) and I asked him: did you want to go to the mall because you missed the freedom of going to stores on a whim and doing what you pleased? His answer: No. I really was just lazy!

@Beth in Greenbelt

I didn't want to say and make people jealous, but my husband is totally the laundry person too!! 😍 I honestly can't remember the last time I did it!! He doesn't have a specific day though, just depends what's else is going on. It probably is often Monday or Tuesday though because he works many weekends.

The only time I'm in danger of running out is when he has to be away for 2 weeks at a time, but that's only once a year. ☺️

